skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "397434d7-49db-4a5c-9e6b-c360f0107162", "value": "Evidence of past environmental conditions, eg insect, seed, pollen remains"}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "86b78db6-68ca-46a7-a516-d1ad9d6861c2", "value": "FISH Evidence Thesaurus"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "45e943f6-7f34-483a-b2da-eafaa45fce99", "value": "Terminology covering the existing physical remains of a monument, or the means by which a monument has been identified where no physical remains exist"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "895e1648-ff35-4e65-acf8-d3dc1d89d117", "value": "Monument visible, usually from the air, due to the fill of features being of a different colour than the surrounding subsoil. Soilmarks show up well in ploughed fields or areas where the topsoil has been stripped. Term derived from AN32 Glossary"}
{"id": "c48e951a-b6db-475b-96b3-35a86596e6fa", "value": "Natural feature or area deliberately enhanced to construct a monument, eg rock carving, cave, rock shelter."}
{"id": "9a3ca8b3-8b4b-45b4-972c-d1e3dc7b1340", "value": "The fragmentary or substantial remains of a vehicle or aircraft. Where recovered from excavation double index with SUB SURFACE DEPOSIT."}

{"id": "68d01bbc-80b4-4779-bba5-52e9d5626534", "value": "An object such as an organ, display case or piece of furniture such as a pew, usually associated with a larger monument but which may be found in isolation. For example a war memorial roll of honour in its display case."}

{"id": "7a801c24-88b0-42eb-8fe7-6de05e580a7e", "value": "Man-made roofless edifice or construction which is intact or substantially intact, with significant survival of original features, even if no longer serving original intended function."}

{"id": "7f50ec56-daab-40e1-8cf0-965187551683", "value": "A monument consisting of a built structure, but which has been demolished so that only a ground plan and foundations, or similar, are thought to remain. Where all below ground traces have also been removed use DESTROYED MONUMENT."}

{"id": "b79b827c-c290-466d-a039-14dfe17366ec", "value": "Man-made, roofless edifice or construction visible as substantial above-ground remains retaining evidence of architecture and materials, but which has been substantially destroyed."}

{"id": "b07ca4d8-c699-48f8-a066-7bf1682a92d0", "value": "A man-made construction or object (such as a gravestone) which has been moved from its original site either through active human intervention or natural processes such as erosion. For buildings which have been moved use MOVED BUILDING."}
{"id": "cb1e1bb3-c64e-4dc1-ad35-c3ea27e7489d", "value": "Man-made building, edifice or construction of assembled material parts."}
{"id": "13f8db79-86c0-4f6c-bacf-30c30bb02580", "value": "An object lying on the sea bed detected by marine survey equipment that emits and receives high frequency sound waves."}
{"id": "285a5b27-33dc-482e-bf6f-4ef1f005d4ad", "value": "A monument visible as a trace on marine survey equipment"}

{"id": "4e669b27-46d2-4b6b-9024-88df300e5c8b", "value": "Maritime monument identified as a ferrous object lying on the sea bed detected using marine surveying equipment that detects localised anomalies in the Earth's magnetic field."}
{"id": "f84de97f-db09-4d81-9c5b-29fba96594f4", "value": "An object in the sea bed detected by marine survey equipment that shows the contours of the sea bed beneath a vessel."}

{"id": "83912d6b-1473-4045-a6b0-bc75b04c6002", "value": "A marine survey in which a multi-element transducer provides many (30-150) individual soundings of the water depth and echo strength for each ping."}

{"id": "fa6383c3-9e29-4cc1-92b9-e6549b72cd5a", "value": "An object projecting out of the sea bed detected by marine survey equipment that emits and receives high frequency sound waves projected sideways from a boat or towed array."}

{"id": "d3e43183-22e0-41c4-ac66-953693b126db", "value": "Monument either never or no longer visible above ground surface, but whose presence is indicated by proven below ground stratigraphy revealed by deliberate investigation, including geophysical survey, or other surface disturbance."}
{"id": "cf4e982a-63d7-49d3-9e91-68191985a846", "value": "Monument visible on the sea, lake or river bed, either totally submerged at all times, or exposed at low tide, low water conditions etc."}
{"id": "69e61369-c574-44bd-9249-13a5e4543b31", "value": "Monument thought to be archaeological or historical but proved to be natural."}
{"id": "dbb43538-c49d-425e-b6a8-c3dc7689acb4", "value": "Monument with a roof and walls or evidence of these."}

{"id": "0c214d29-498b-4eec-8c53-c0af1c04ccc5", "value": "A monument composed of plants or trees which are still extant. Especially relevant for park and garden features. For example tree avenue, orchard, rose garden and lawn."}

{"id": "4f297fe3-7788-4f46-8f72-dd8d4a6adc90", "value": "Monument whose existence is inferred from the traces of architectural features. Eg include shadow marks on building walls or beams, pillars, floors incorporated into a later structure, suggesting the existence of an earlier building."}

{"id": "2279cdf0-3367-47d3-9512-b4599f6b38a8", "value": "A landscape which has been specifically designed or modified. Often indicated by proven below ground stratigraphy, revealed by deliberate investigation including geophysical survey, or other surface monuments or structures."}
{"id": "7e105299-f5a8-47a9-9629-ae390b966dcd", "value": "Monument visible as a below ground man-made structure. Use for tunnels, mineworking, cellars, shelters."}
{"id": "58983eed-a63d-4cc5-8207-5f39f7628986", "value": "Feature visible following archaeological excavation"}
{"id": "8cef8c61-cfd1-4203-9a47-db33eaf24572", "value": "Not to be used for indexing. Broad term used to assist retreival of all monuments where physical evidence is recorded."}

{"id": "e2decc7a-a29b-43c0-8d6e-6191e42fe210", "value": "An element such as a window, door or wall decoration, usually associated with a larger monument but which may be found in isolation. For example a stained glass window or panelling saved from a demolished building."}

{"id": "31fd1fdf-ffe9-4232-9d30-d378e6ebdd64", "value": "The deliberate deposit of a body in the ground, usually located in a special area set aside for the purpose of burial, such as a graveyard or cemetery."}

{"id": "48f86342-a061-4297-ae3e-6d96f47e2392", "value": "Monument visible as a mark in standing crops or parchmarks, but where no subsurface deposits have been proven eg by excavation or other ground disturbance, in which case SUB SURFACE DEPOSIT should be used."}

{"id": "f8d7ea4a-c587-4816-a89d-f9448330cd6a", "value": "A monument where the evidence that defines the type of the monument derives from the nature of surface markings. Examples include graffitti on quarry walls."}

{"id": "28a7f258-eddc-451b-801a-c45da95d9883", "value": "Monument whose existence is indicated by the discovery of isolated artefacts or an artefact scatter. Eg a scatter of roofing tiles indicating the presence of a building. Use narrow terms where circumstances of discovery are known."}
{"id": "093a9929-05ee-49ef-8fa4-df26e480a9d5", "value": "A deposit that forms the ground surface (when the evidence is collected), particularly a hard surface such as a floor or road."}

{"id": "20010698-6d38-489e-a526-a2f880d57169", "value": "Monument existing as an upstanding earthwork, ditch or artificial watercourse, or as a low stone built feature not covered by the other categories."}
{"id": "184181ae-b44f-414c-ab2d-88f77c170149", "value": "A maritime monument where the hull structure and fabric of a vessel remain wholly or mainly intact."}
{"id": "74c4732b-3cd8-4878-a3c6-1c69860a8c4c", "value": "A maritime monument where the fabric of a vessel has collapsed, leaving the hull structure flat on the sea bed but not widely dispersed."}
{"id": "0adffd69-1424-418c-9758-289b93b92898", "value": "A maritime monument where the vessel remains are buried in the sea bed."}
{"id": "e9405471-43c0-4cab-96af-3d57709917b0", "value": "Monument visible as remains of former earthworks."}

{"id": "c99e771c-6e16-4fcd-a53d-fe08bdcf89f5", "value": "Monument type/interpretation is inferred, based on informed speculation eg by comparison with similar monuments, proximity to other monuments, topography, site character etc."}

{"id": "5ec1b7d7-a316-4a06-8aa1-4cf05a1072d6", "value": "A monument previously consisting of a built structure, but which has been demolished, such that only a ground plan and foundations or similar are thought to remain. Where all below ground traces have also been removed use DESTROYED MONUMENT."}
{"id": "871bdca7-b64d-4c69-a5c3-f94f6ba2372e", "value": "Use where the presence or nature of a monument is inferred from placenames or placename elements."}
{"id": "672fb5b4-1301-46a4-a791-5935460f5786", "value": "An object in the sea bed recorded on the Hydrographic Office plot of objects snagged by nets during trawling."}
{"id": "00af6253-9605-402b-ac81-c97fcec271b1", "value": "Not to be used for indexing. Broad term to assist retreival of all monuments where non-physical evidence is recorded."}
{"id": "fa04f4cf-5b6f-40c8-8056-63673b413a69", "value": "A monument whose presence is inferred from verbally delivered information drawn from the speaker's personal knowledge."}

{"id": "016b9da4-3bca-40a1-9178-23d83c1dc6f0", "value": "Monument known only from primary documentary sources eg books, maps, legal records, where no physical evidence exists. Use also where a monument has been planned but never constructed."}

{"id": "0f96c813-ab64-49d1-a660-6a5346bef53d", "value": "Monument visible as substantial above ground remains, retaining evidence of architecture and materials, with walls partially or completely intact but with roof and interior walls substantially or completely destroyed."}
{"id": "5e5d0fbf-ebda-484a-b7bf-c74e3c06628a", "value": "A distribution of artefacts indicating the presence, or former presence, of a monument."}
{"id": "5a3778b3-62a4-4b59-ba4a-4c9c2b204a2c", "value": "A maritime monument where the hull of a vessel is mostly in one piece, with large pieces of the superstructure intact."}
{"id": "c275f9e1-8860-41f0-a9d6-400a774fef36", "value": "A maritime monument where the remains of a vessel are known to exist but where no detailed information is available."}
{"id": "ed6acba3-4970-4f54-b809-3657dff436b8", "value": "A maritime monument where the remains of a vessel are scattered over a wide area."}
{"id": "52b7758c-4005-4596-95d5-9933ea473e62", "value": "Current recorded information does not give the evidence for a monument, or the information is regarded as unreliable."}

{"id": "d37c8d15-8750-46f2-814d-3f091f683216", "value": "All physical evidence for a monument has certainly been completely destroyed (allowing no future reinvestigation) by activity implying substantial ground disturbance. Eg quarrying, road cutting, or natural disaster, erosion, acts of God etc."}
{"id": "ba66cb8e-ec46-4271-b4da-322b7d75042d", "value": "Do not use"}

{"id": "33edfffe-0bbe-4a31-99d5-40462e420e08", "value": "A building which has been moved from its original site either through active human intervention or natural processes such as erosion. For structures or objects such as gravestones use MOVED STRUCTURE."}

{"id": "9953986e-ddfb-4ba2-9103-de33f758ec15", "value": "Monument with roof or walls intact or substantially intact, significant survival of original features, even if building no longer in use for original function."}
{"id": "577edf3b-e31f-4e14-8c7b-945e9aaf6258", "value": "Monument whose presence is inferred by discovery of unstratified artefacts, for instance in plough soil."}

{"id": "01bd122f-f2a3-4c31-b5c7-8cc8c7d6419a", "value": "A Monument whose presence is inferred from artefacts found in stratified below ground deposits, as distinct from surface collection or chance find."}
